Which file structure will be more close to a relational database?

Delimited (CSV files)

Is AVRO the same thing as JSON, what is the difference?

More information is contained AVRO than JSON
AVRO has more metadata describing the data
(no column value, also protocol communication)

What is the difference between PARQUET and a delimited file type?

Parquet is more efficient
Parquet has a complex nested structure with lower storage costs
Parquet also has a better compression therefore shines with bigger data sets.

Which kind of compression algorithm allows to consume data using parallel processing?

bzip2 

Define a scenario where ACID properties are needed, enlist 3 reasons why.

1 - no tolerance to error
2 - consistancy
3 - speed is not critical in the process

Definie a scenario where BASE properties are needed, enlist 3 reasons why.

1 - High speed of processing
2 - Tolerance for errors
3 - Flexibility & accepts data that is not consistant
4 - avoid deadlock or system slowdowns


